  "text": ". For example, in Ferich sediment the rate of TRIS formation in the present study could only be sustained for 72 d if 50% of initial RFe(II) (ratio similar to [CITATION_1] ) from the 0 to 2 cm interval was available for precipitation. However, if infauna facilitates mobilization of Fe 2+ from sediment down to 10 cm depth, the rate of TRIS formation can potentially be sustained for 375 d. It has similarly been estimated that TRIS formation can be sustained for up to 160 d in a eutrophic coastal lagoon with high SR [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] and up to 120 d in diffusion-controlled sediment mesocosms ).",
